{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn essential sound and haptic design principles and concepts for creating meaningful and delightful experiences that engage a wider range of human senses. Discover how to combine audio and haptics, using the Taptic Engine, to add a new level of realism and improve feedback in your app or game."}],"metadata":{"title":"Designing Audio-Haptic Experiences","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC19"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19"]]},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (26 min)","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc19\/810","isActive":true}},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-810-Designing-AudioHaptic-Experiences","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"What is an Audio Haptic Experience?","level":2,"anchor":"What-is-an-Audio-Haptic-Experience"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some tones are so low that our ears cannot hear, however real speakers still produce a vibration that our body is still able to catch."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"One of the reasons behind the iPhone Taptic Engine is to reproduce those low frequency sounds\/vibrations.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Taptic Engine works in sync with the iPhone speaker, resulting in an Audio Haptic Experience."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Three Guiding Principles","level":2,"anchor":"Three-Guiding-Principles"},{"type":"heading","text":"Causality","level":3,"anchor":"Causality"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For feedback to be useful, it must be obvious what it caused it.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For example a soccer hitting a ball:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"cause: foot colliding with the ball.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"effect: sound of impact, feel of impact"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When designing sound\/haptics for your experience, think about what it’d feel\/sound like if what we interact with was a physical object.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Harmony","level":3,"anchor":"Harmony"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Things should feel the way they look the way they sound."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Utility","level":3,"anchor":"Utility"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add audio and haptics that provide clear value to your app experience."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Written By","level":2,"anchor":"Written-By"},{"type":"row","columns":[{"size":1,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"zntfdr","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"size":4,"content":[{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Federico-Zanetello","text":"Federico Zanetello"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Contributed Notes"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/zntfdr.dev","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"numberOfColumns":5},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Missing anything? Corrections? ","type":"text"},{"type":